The paper discusses the design of training waveforms for continuous phase modulation (CPM) in wireless communications, which falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Golay complementary pairs, which are commonly used in spread spectrum communication systems, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category of signal and image processing (cs.SI).
